 Pok\u00e9mon will be blessed with eternal love."},{"version":"y","text":"During the spawning season, countless Luvdisc congregate at coral reefs, turning the waters pink."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pok\u00e9mon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean\u2019s waves."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Luvdisc\u2019s heart-shaped body is a symbol of love and romance. It is said that any couple meeting this Pok\u00e9mon is promised a loving relationship that never ends."},{"version":"sun","text":"If a Luvdisc is left on its own, it becomes despondent, leaving itself open to attack. That is when Pelipper snatch them up."},{"version":"moon","text":"Loving couples have a soft spot for this Pok\u00e9mon, so honeymoon hotels often release this Pok\u00e9mon into their pools."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"There was an era when it was overfished due to the rumor that having one of its heart-shaped scales would enable you to find a sweetheart."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"Luvdisc makes its home in coral reefs in warm seas. It especially likes sleeping in the space between Corsola\u2019s branches."}],"evo":{"name":"luvdisc","level":0,"min_level":null,"trigger":null,"item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":null,"turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[]},"sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/370.png","shiny":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/shiny/370.png","capture":225,"happiness":70,"growth":"fast","gender":6,"hatch":20,"ev":{"speed":1},"forms":[]}